name: phosphomethylpyrimidine synthase
comment: Binds a [4Fe-4S] cluster that is coordinated by 3 cysteines and an exchangeable S-adenosyl-L-methionine molecule. The first stage of catalysis is reduction of the S-adenosyl-L-methionine to produce L-methionine and a 5'-deoxyadenosin-5'-yl radical that is crucial for the conversion of the substrate. Part of the pathway for thiamine biosynthesis.

references.title: Reconstitution of ThiC in thiamine pyrimidine biosynthesis expands the radical SAM superfamily.
